Here is why your LinkedIn requests are not getting accepted -

YOU ARE NOT CUSTOMIZING THEM!!!
The more you personalize your invitation, more is the chance that your messages will be accepted. Here is a templates -

Hello <<Their name>>,

I am currently pursuing masters from <<university>>. I had a chance to watch one of your recent videos on <<topic>> and I found it super helpful and inspiring. 

It would like to connect with you on LinkedIn to follow your career journey and learn from you.

Thank you in advance for connecting!

<<your name>>

Don’t forget to save this video, and follow me for more!

How to stand out in your interview - 

1) do your research and prepare very well for the interviews
Be ready to talk about yourself, your previous experience, and why you are the best candidate for the job.

2) Ask intelligent questions
This demonstrates that you have done your research very well, and you understand the company‘s business and how they work.

3) Be authentic and be yourself.
Recruiters talk to candidates on a day-to-day basis and when somebody is not being themselves it’s pretty evident to them. Being authentic also brings a sense of confidence that is very important to crack the interviews.
